    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>it's not just burnout though. it's deeper. it's like the whole point of being here was to create, and if the well is dry, then what is the purpose of the vessel? i look at people just... existing. eating, sleeping, working, repeating. it looks so hollow. it feels like i'm just a ghost inhabiting a body that's waiting for a reason to stay, but there isn't one. does that even make sense? or am i just being dramatic?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
